# UI Design System â€” Mandatory Rules

All UI code in `apps/web/` MUST follow these rules. Violations break visual consistency across themes.

## 1. Color: ONLY use CSS variables

NEVER hardcode colors. Always use `var(--token-name)`.

| Purpose | Token | Example |
|---------|-------|---------|
| Page background | `--bg-color` | `background: var(--bg-color)` |
| Card/panel background | `--panel-bg` | `background: var(--panel-bg)` |
| Sidebar background | `--sidebar-bg` | |
| Primary text | `--text-primary` | `color: var(--text-primary)` |
| Secondary text | `--text-secondary` | |
| Tertiary/disabled text | `--text-tertiary` | |
| Accent/link/primary action | `--accent` | |
| Accent RGB (for rgba()) | `--accent-rgb` | `rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.15)` |
| Accent hover | `--accent-hover` | |
| Success | `--success` | |
| Danger/error | `--danger` | |
| Warning | `--warning` | |
| Border (general) | `--border` | |
| Panel border | `--panel-border` | |
| Sidebar border | `--sidebar-border` | |
| Panel shadow | `--panel-shadow` | |
| Glass blur | `--glass-blur` | |

For tinted backgrounds (e.g. success badge bg), use `color-mix()`:
```css
background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--success) 15%, transparent);
```

NEVER use raw `rgba(52, 199, 89, 0.15)` â€” these break in non-default themes.

## 2. Typography

| Element | Font Size | Weight | Class |
|---------|-----------|--------|-------|
| Body default | 13px | 400 | (inherited) |
| Page title | 20px | 600 | `.ios-title` |
| Subtitle | 13px | 400 | `.ios-subtitle` |
| Secondary text | 13px | 400 | `.small` |
| Table header | 11px | 600 | `th` (global) |
| Table cell | 13px | 400 | `td` (global) |
| Button text | 15px | 600 | `button` (global) |
| Input text | 15px | 400 | `input` (global) |
| Status pill | 11px | 700 | `.status` |
| Stat value | 24px | 700 | (inline) |
| Heading (h1-h6) | varies | 600 | (global, letter-spacing: -0.02em) |

Font stack: `-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "SF Pro Display", "SF Pro Text", "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif`

NEVER set a different font-family. The `theme-antigravity` engine overrides to serif automatically.

## 3. Spacing

| Context | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Main content padding | `32px 40px` |
| Sidebar padding | `20px 12px` |
| Card padding (default) | `24px` |
| Card padding (compact) | `16px` |
| Table header cell | `12px 16px` |
| Table body cell | `8px 16px` |
| Button padding | `10px 18px` |
| Input padding | `10px 12px` |
| Section gap (header â†’ content) | `24px` |
| Inline element gap | `8px` or `12px` |
| Stat badge padding | `16px` |

## 4. Border Radius

ALWAYS use CSS variables â€” themes override these to 0px (terminal, cyberpunk, brutalism).

| Token | Default | Usage |
|-------|---------|-------|
| `--border-radius-lg` | 6px | Cards, panels |
| `--border-radius-md` | 4px | Table wraps, inputs |
| `--border-radius-sm` | 2px | Badges, small elements |
| `999px` | pill | Buttons, status pills (hardcoded OK) |

## 5. Shadows

ALWAYS use `var(--panel-shadow)` for card/panel shadows. NEVER hardcode shadow values.

## 6. Component Patterns

### Use existing UI components:
- `<Card>` â€” wraps content in `.ios-card`
- `<Badge variant="success|danger|warning|info">` â€” semantic badge
- `<StatBadge label="..." value={...}>` â€” metric display
- `<PageHeader title="..." subtitle="...">` â€” page header

### Styling approach:
- **Layout**: Use CSS classes (`.header`, `.ios-card`, `.card`, `.table-wrap`) + inline `style` for flex/grid
- **Colors/borders/shadows**: ALWAYS via CSS variables in inline styles
- **Typography**: Use CSS classes (`.ios-title`, `.ios-subtitle`, `.small`, `.status`)
- **Spacing**: Inline `style` with values from the spacing table above

### Dark mode:
- Use `.dark` class on `:root`, NOT `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)`
- All CSS variables auto-switch â€” no manual dark mode logic needed in components
- If you must detect dark mode in JS, use `document.documentElement.classList.contains('dark')`

## 7. Forbidden Patterns

- `color: '#007aff'` â€” use `var(--accent)`
- `background: 'rgba(52, 199, 89, 0.15)'` â€” use `color-mix(in srgb, var(--success) 15%, transparent)`
- `font-family: 'Inter'` or any custom font â€” use inherited system font
- `border-radius: 8` without using a token â€” use `var(--border-radius-lg)`
- `box-shadow: '0 2px 8px ...'` â€” use `var(--panel-shadow)`
- `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` in new code â€” use `.dark` selector
- Creating new CSS variables without adding them to ALL theme definitions in `globals.css`

## 8. Adding New Tokens

If you need a new design token:
1. Add it to `:root` in `globals.css`
2. Add dark mode override in `:root.dark`
3. Add overrides in ALL 8 theme engines (terminal, cyberpunk, brutalism, antigravity, solarized-light, vsc-dark, vsc-light, monokai)
4. Add it to `apps/web/lib/design-tokens.ts`
5. Document it in this file

## 9. Design System Compliance Checklist (for new pages)

Before submitting any new page or component, verify:
- [ ] All colors use `var(--*)` or `color-mix()` â€” zero hardcoded `#hex` or `rgba()`
- [ ] Typography uses established classes (`.ios-title`, `.ios-subtitle`, `.small`, `.status`) or `design-tokens.ts` sizes
- [ ] Spacing matches the spacing table above
- [ ] Border radius uses `var(--border-radius-*)` tokens
- [ ] Shadows use `var(--panel-shadow)` only
- [ ] Cards use `<Card>` component or `.ios-card` class
- [ ] Page header uses `<PageHeader>` component
- [ ] Metrics use `<StatBadge>` component
- [ ] Badges use `<Badge>` component with semantic variants
- [ ] No `@media (prefers-color-scheme)` â€” dark mode via `.dark` class only
- [ ] Tested in at least 2 theme engines (default + terminal or cyberpunk)
